in the flower of his youth...

582
00:40:38,002 --> 00:40:40,881
"Flower"?
Dobson is more vegetable material.

583
00:40:40,938 --> 00:40:43,544
- (stifled laugh)
- Alex: Was.

584
00:40:43,607 --> 00:40:44,950
Must have killed himself.

585
00:40:45,009 --> 00:40:47,285
Headmaster:
His brother, sister...

586
00:40:47,344 --> 00:40:48,414
- What?
- Colin: Shit.

587
00:40:48,479 --> 00:40:53,360
Finn, you're unusually quiet
this afternoon.

588
00:40:53,417 --> 00:40:56,796
I'm not sure I can add
anything to the debate, sir.

589
00:40:58,556 --> 00:41:01,230
Will wonders never cease?

590
00:41:01,292 --> 00:41:03,101
I don't find
the historian's need

591
00:41:03,160 --> 00:41:04,833
to ascribe responsibility

592
00:41:04,895 --> 00:41:07,068
a particularly fruitful arena, sir.

593
00:41:08,365 --> 00:41:10,072
Care to elaborate?

594
00:41:11,635 --> 00:41:13,581
Historians yearn for an answer
to the question

595
00:41:13,637 --> 00:41:15,583
of who's to blame for this event

596
00:41:15,639 --> 00:41:19,416
or for that atrocity, but...
I don't know, sir.

597
00:41:19,477 --> 00:41:23,482
Sometimes it seems to me
it is impossible to know.

598
00:41:23,547 --> 00:41:24,924
Go on.

599
00:41:24,982 --> 00:41:27,485
Well, Patrick Lagrange,
sir, said that,

600
00:41:27,551 --> 00:41:29,895
"History is the certainty
produced at the point

601
00:41:29,954 --> 00:41:31,865
when the imperfections of memory

602
00:41:31,922 --> 00:41:33,924
meet the inadequacies
of documentation."

603
00:41:33,991 --> 00:41:35,971
It's the lies of victors, sir.

604
00:41:37,394 --> 00:41:39,635
As long as you understand
that it is also

605
00:41:39,697 --> 00:41:41,574
the delusions of the defeated.

606
00:41:41,632 --> 00:41:44,112
Adrian:
Take Dobson's suicide, sir.

607
00:41:47,471 --> 00:41:48,882
