is that nothing can now be known

614
00:42:06,957 --> 00:42:09,335
in the absence
of Dobson's own testimony.

615
00:42:09,393 --> 00:42:11,236
We...

616
00:42:11,295 --> 00:42:13,332
we may never know the truth.

617
00:42:13,397 --> 00:42:14,899
And...

618
00:42:14,965 --> 00:42:18,606
no amount of intellectual posturing
can alter that.

619
00:42:19,837 --> 00:42:22,977
Do you see the problem, sir?

620
00:42:23,040 --> 00:42:26,283
Finn, I see the problem,
thank you.

621
00:42:26,343 --> 00:42:30,758
Camus says that suicide is
the only true philosophical question.

622
00:42:32,249 --> 00:42:35,526
Apart from ethics,
politics, aesthetics,

623
00:42:35,586 --> 00:42:37,190
and all that other stuff.

624
00:42:37,254 --> 00:42:39,294
All that other stuff
we're learning about in school.

625
00:42:39,323 --> 00:42:41,034
- About the beauty and wisdom...
- The only true one.

626
00:42:41,058 --> 00:42:43,629
The essential one on which
all the others depend.

627
00:42:45,296 --> 00:42:48,140
When we left school
and went our separate ways,

628
00:42:48,198 --> 00:42:50,041
out of everyone,
Adrian was the only one

