I will have a tea.

767
00:56:46,035 --> 00:56:47,995
Colin: Excuse me, love,
could we have another tea?

768
00:56:51,674 --> 00:56:53,449
Blimey.

769
00:56:53,510 --> 00:56:55,046
What a nut job.

770
00:56:55,111 --> 00:56:56,886
What ever did you see in her?

771
00:56:56,946 --> 00:56:58,948
You and Adrian both.

772
00:56:59,015 --> 00:57:02,622
Well, you know,
she was very mysterious.

773
00:57:02,685 --> 00:57:03,755
(chuckles)

774
00:57:03,820 --> 00:57:05,800
You know, the great irony,
of course,

775
00:57:05,855 --> 00:57:08,199
was that it was you
that introduced them.

776
00:57:08,258 --> 00:57:09,464
Introduced who?

777
00:57:09,526 --> 00:57:11,301
Adrian and Veronica.

778
00:57:11,361 --> 00:57:14,865
No, Adrian met Veronica
through her brother Jack.

779
00:57:14,931 --> 00:57:17,912
Oh, wishful thinking,
my old friend.

780
00:57:17,967 --> 00:57:18,968
No.

781
00:57:19,035 --> 00:57:21,140
Yeah, Adrian and Jack
were at Cambridge together.

782
00:57:21,204 --> 00:57:22,342
But that's not how they met.

783
00:57:22,405 --> 00:57:25,045
No, it was your fault
that they got together.

784
00:57:25,108 --> 00:57:27,019
- Hole-in-one.
- No, no, no.

785
00:57:27,076 --> 00:57:28,453
You came up to town from Bristol

786
00:57:28,511 --> 00:57:30,616
with your ladylove
and you met all of us.

787
00:57:30,680 --> 00:57:34,184
Yeah, chomping at the bit
to introduce the love of your life.

788
00:57:35,652 --> 00:57:38,565
Oh, I could've sworn
they met through Jack.

789
00:57:38,621 --> 00:57:40,362
Afraid not.
(chuckles)

790
00:57:40,423 --> 00:57:43,370
I'm surprised you haven't had a good
rummage through the Webster albums.

791
00:57:43,426 --> 00:57:45,599
If memory serves,
you were always snapping away.

792
00:57:46,229 --> 00:57:50,803
Hmm. They must have been
deemed surplus to requirements.

793
00:58:09,219 --> 00:58:11,426
Colin:
Mm, that's a pity, old bean.

794
00:58:11,488 --> 00:58:14,526
Alex:
So have you... have you tried

795
00:58:14,591 --> 00:58:18,300
- contacting her directly?
- How?

796
00:58:19,395 --> 00:58:21,500
- She's not there. Try Jack.
- Okay.

797
00:58:21,564 --> 00:58:23,305
(keyboard clacking)

798
00:58:23,366 --> 00:58:24,504
Mm-hmm.

799
00:58:25,235 --> 00:58:26,270
Oh...

800
00:58:27,203 --> 00:58:28,580
Oh, right.

801
00:58:28,638 --> 00:58:29,946
Loads of them.

802
00:58:30,006 --> 00:58:31,007
(exhales)

803
00:58:31,074 --> 00:58:32,075
What about...

804
00:58:32,141 --> 00:58:34,052
- What that...
- This one?

805
00:58:34,110 --> 00:58:35,111
Oh, it's him.

806
00:58:35,178 --> 00:58:36,179
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

807
00:58:36,246 --> 00:58:37,247
Yeah, yeah.

808
00:58:37,313 --> 00:58:38,314
Wow.

809
00:58:38,381 --> 00:58:39,425
- God.
- Where on earth is he?

810
00:58:39,449 --> 00:58:40,860
Cricket.

811
00:58:40,917 --> 00:58:42,021
- Tennis, no?
- Tennis.

812
00:58:42,085 --> 00:58:43,496
- Oh, look.
- (laughs)

813
00:58:43,553 --> 00:58:44,554
All: Mm.

814
00:58:44,621 --> 00:58:46,123
- Who's that?
- I don't know.

815
00:58:46,189 --> 00:58:47,190
This is very nice.

816
00:58:47,257 --> 00:58:49,066
He looks as self-satisfied
as he ever did.

817
00:58:49,125 --> 00:58:50,433
(laughs)

818
00:58:51,661 --> 00:58:53,140
All: Oh...

819
00:58:53,196 --> 00:58:54,607
- Oh!
- (laughing)

820
00:58:56,266 --> 00:58:58,041
Do you want to
send him a message?

821
00:58:58,101 --> 00:59:01,571
- Isn't that a bit much?
- No, it'd be rude not to.

822
00:59:03,406 --> 00:59:05,852
Do people really
communicate this way?

823
00:59:05,909 --> 00:59:07,946
Yours truly
communicates this way.

824
00:59:08,011 --> 00:59:09,012
- Really?
- Yeah.

825
00:59:09,078 --> 00:59:11,649
L-I got in touch with a woman
I'd been at university with.

826
00:59:11,714 --> 00:59:13,591
Hadn't seen her for
the best part of 40 years.

827
00:59:13,650 --> 00:59:16,460
We met up,
got on like a house on fire.

828
00:59:16,519 --> 00:59:19,830
- Oh, great.
- You see, it's a boon for us widowers.

829
00:59:19,889 --> 00:59:21,334
- Mm.
- Hmm.

830
00:59:21,391 --> 00:59:22,392
There you go.

831
00:59:22,458 --> 00:59:23,869
- Sent.
- (computer chimes)

832
00:59:23,927 --> 00:59:25,873
Oh, done.

833
00:59:25,929 --> 00:59:27,909
- What?
- You're in now.

834
00:59:27,964 --> 00:59:31,309
Welcome to the 21 st century,
Mr. Webster.

835
00:59:31,367 --> 00:59:32,505
Oh, blimey.

836
00:59:32,569 --> 00:59:34,378
- Ta-Ra.
- (rain pattering)

837
00:59:37,206 --> 00:59:40,312
- Tell us how it all turns out.
- Certainly will.

838
00:59:40,376 --> 00:59:41,878
Don't let it get to you, old bean.

839
00:59:41,945 --> 00:59:43,549
Insightful as always.

840
00:59:47,417 --> 00:59:49,658
Alex:
Henry VIII.

841
00:59:49,719 --> 00:59:52,529
"Now, which one of you
young bright things can offer

842
00:59:52,589 --> 00:59:54,330
a characterization of the age?

843
00:59:54,390 --> 00:59:55,391
Simpson?"

844
00:59:55,458 --> 00:59:57,199
Colin:
I'd say there was unrest, sir.

845
00:59:57,260 --> 00:59:59,900
(stammers) I'd even say
there was great unrest, sir.

846
00:59:59,963 --> 01:00:02,000
(Colin and Alex laughing)

847
01:00:07,437 --> 01:00:09,508
(indistinct chattering)

848
01:00:09,572 --> 01:00:12,143
(music playing)

849
01:00:19,148 --> 01:00:22,322
<i>♪ I feel so sad,
I feel depressed ♪</i>

850
01:00:24,787 --> 01:00:28,291
<i>♪ 'Cause you're the best girl
that I've ever had ♪</i>

851
01:00:30,593 --> 01:00:34,336
<i>♪ I can't get your love,
I can't get affection ♪</i>

852
01:00:36,766 --> 01:00:41,010
<i>♪ Oh, little girl,
psychotic reaction ♪</i>

853
01:00:41,070 --> 01:00:43,175
<i>♪ And it feels like this ♪</i>

854
01:00:43,239 --> 01:00:44,946
(camera clicking)

855
01:00:58,121 --> 01:01:00,624
Not enjoying the party?

856
01:01:00,690 --> 01:01:02,294
(phone ringing)

857
01:01:02,358 --> 01:01:04,065
(clock ticking)

858
01:01:04,127 --> 01:01:05,970
(phone continues ringing)

859
01:01:16,606 --> 01:01:18,176
Oh, shit.

860
01:01:20,576 --> 01:01:22,556
(answering machine beeps)

861
01:01:23,212 --> 01:01:24,423
Tony on answering machine:
Hello, you have reached

862
01:01:24,447 --> 01:01:25,924
- telephone of Anthony Webster.
- Bollocks!

863
01:01:25,948 --> 01:01:27,518
I'm unable to take your call now.

864
01:01:27,583 --> 01:01:29,494
Please leave me a message
after the beep,

865
01:01:29,552 --> 01:01:32,089
and I will return your call
at my earliest convenience.

866
01:01:32,155 --> 01:01:33,361
- Thank you.
- (grunts)

867
01:01:33,423 --> 01:01:35,801
(answering machine beeps)

868
01:01:35,858 --> 01:01:37,132
Woman: Hello.

869
01:01:37,193 --> 01:01:40,697
This is Veronica Ford.

870
01:01:40,763 --> 01:01:44,336
I am in receipt of
all your correspondence,

871
01:01:44,400 --> 01:01:46,812
and I also understand
from my brother

872
01:01:46,869 --> 01:01:49,406
that you wish to meet
to discuss my mother's estate.

873
01:01:51,040 --> 01:01:52,951
I will be in town this morning.

874
01:01:54,644 --> 01:01:57,181
I will see you at
the wobbly bridge at 9:00 a.m.

875
01:01:58,748 --> 01:01:59,749
(line clicks)

876
01:02:00,850 --> 01:02:02,386
(beeps)

877
01:02:06,155 --> 01:02:08,260
- Shit.
- (phone beeps)

878
01:02:10,927 --> 01:02:12,929
(buzzing)

879
01:02:27,243 --> 01:02:28,381
(water sloshing)

880
01:02:29,712 --> 01:02:33,250
<i>♪ Time has told me ♪</i>

881
01:02:36,452 --> 01:02:40,093
<i>♪ You're a rare, rare find I</i>

882
01:02:43,059 --> 01:02:46,973
<i>♪ Trouble cure ♪</i>

883
01:02:47,029 --> 01:02:49,236
Could I get a glass
of red wine, please?

884
01:02:49,298 --> 01:02:52,836
<i>♪ For a troubled mind ♪</i>

885
01:02:52,902 --> 01:02:54,745
(indistinct conversations)

886
01:02:56,105 --> 01:02:59,484
<i>♪ And time has told me ♪</i>

887
01:03:02,411 --> 01:03:06,325
<i>♪ Not to ask for more ♪</i>

888
01:03:08,885 --> 01:03:12,332
<i>♪ For some day our ocean ♪</i>

889
01:03:13,089 --> 01:03:14,830
(giggling)

890
01:03:14,891 --> 01:03:17,735
<i>♪ Will find its shore... ♪</i>

891
01:03:17,794 --> 01:03:19,740
Are you...

892
01:03:19,796 --> 01:03:21,275
are you sure?

893
01:03:22,098 --> 01:03:23,805
Really, Anthony.

894
01:03:26,135 --> 01:03:28,581
You said it didn't feel right
when we were going out.

895
01:03:28,638 --> 01:03:30,709
No, it didn't... then.

896
01:03:32,074 --> 01:03:33,849
But it does now?

897
01:03:38,347 --> 01:03:40,190
I don't know.

898
01:03:43,286 --> 01:03:45,323
You're quite cowardly,
aren't you?

899
01:03:48,457 --> 01:03:51,904
<i>♪ Time has told me ♪</i>

900
01:03:54,430 --> 01:03:58,139
<i>♪ You came with the dawn ♪</i>

901
01:04:00,937 --> 01:04:04,612
<i>♪ A soul with no footprint... ♪</i>

902
01:04:07,844 --> 01:04:09,414
Veronica?

903
01:04:13,916 --> 01:04:16,795
- Hello, Anthony.
- You look well.

904
01:04:16,853 --> 01:04:18,890
You're bald.

905
01:04:20,790 --> 01:04:22,770
Well, at least it proves
I'm not an alcoholic.

906
01:04:25,027 --> 01:04:26,904
Do people think
you're an alcoholic?

907
01:04:26,963 --> 01:04:29,034
No. No, they don't.

908
01:04:30,132 --> 01:04:32,237
I read somewhere that
if you're a very heavy drinker,

909
01:04:32,301 --> 01:04:35,578
there's something in the booze
that stops your hair from falling out.

910
01:04:39,775 --> 01:04:41,652
Shall we find
somewhere to sit down?

911
01:04:42,845 --> 01:04:43,949
Where?

912
01:04:44,013 --> 01:04:46,687
Anywhere?
I'm easy, as you may recall.

913
01:04:53,623 --> 01:04:54,897
Ready to order?

914
01:04:54,957 --> 01:04:57,267
- Um...
- I'll have a fresh mint tea, please.

915
01:04:57,326 --> 01:05:00,034
Um, what sort of coffee
do you serve?

916
01:05:00,096 --> 01:05:01,598
We serve our own blend.

917
01:05:01,664 --> 01:05:03,302
Roasted in our Roastery
in Heme Hill.

918
01:05:03,366 --> 01:05:04,572
Oh, blimey. Uh...

919
01:05:04,634 --> 01:05:06,409
- We don't mess around.
- (chuckles)

920
01:05:06,469 --> 01:05:08,380
Uh, in that case,
I'll have a <i>Macchiato</i>, please.

921
01:05:08,437 --> 01:05:11,008
- Single or double?
- Single, thank you.

922
01:05:11,073 --> 01:05:12,450
Thank you.

923
01:05:15,378 --> 01:05:17,119
Their own blend.

924
01:05:17,179 --> 01:05:19,125
Impressive stuff.
(chuckles)

925
01:05:20,383 --> 01:05:22,385
- (boy exclaiming)
- Woman: Oh!

926
01:05:23,452 --> 01:05:24,863
(wood clacking)

927
01:05:24,921 --> 01:05:27,458
I was sorry to hear about
your mother, Veronica.

928
01:05:28,758 --> 01:05:30,294
Yes.

929
01:05:30,960 --> 01:05:33,964
As, uh, as you're no doubt aware,

930
01:05:34,030 --> 01:05:37,876
it appears that your mother
left something to me in her will.

931
01:05:39,001 --> 01:05:41,174
And when I spoke

932
01:05:41,237 --> 01:05:42,978
with your mother's solicitor...

933
01:05:44,507 --> 01:05:48,353
I was told that the item
that has been left to me was...

934
01:05:48,411 --> 01:05:50,948
um, a diary written by Adrian.

935
01:05:54,951 --> 01:05:58,023
- I don't have the diary.
- Excuse me?

936
01:05:58,087 --> 01:05:59,828
I burnt it.

937
01:06:00,723 --> 01:06:02,600
But it belongs to me.

938
01:06:02,658 --> 01:06:04,236
- It doesn't belong to anyone.
- Boy: Vroom, vroom, vroom!

939
01:06:04,260 --> 01:06:06,103
Look!

940
01:06:06,162 --> 01:06:09,371
I think you'll find that the zoo
is north of the river.

941
01:06:11,334 --> 01:06:13,746
(sighs)
Unbelievable.

942
01:06:16,973 --> 01:06:20,284
Uh... I at least have,

943
01:06:20,343 --> 01:06:23,347
uh, the right to know
what is in it.

944
01:06:24,146 --> 01:06:26,285
Yes'.

945
01:06:27,416 --> 01:06:29,259
Morally, no.

946
01:06:29,318 --> 01:06:33,061
Have you any idea
how unsettling it was for me after,

947
01:06:33,122 --> 01:06:35,659
however many years it's been,

948
01:06:35,725 --> 01:06:38,399
to receive a letter from your mother?

949
01:06:39,328 --> 01:06:42,571
I can't be held accountable
for my mother's actions.

950
01:06:42,631 --> 01:06:44,804
Actually, as executor of her will,

951
01:06:44,867 --> 01:06:47,108
I rather suggest that you can.

952
01:07:12,461 --> 01:07:14,805
What's this?

953
01:07:14,864 --> 01:07:17,105
Because you seem to need
something to read.

954
01:07:19,135 --> 01:07:21,911
- Bye, Anthony.
- I'm-I'm sorry I raised my voice.

955
01:07:51,000 --> 01:07:52,877
(indistinct chattering)

956
01:09:30,533 --> 01:09:32,035
(car lock beeps)

957
01:09:36,772 --> 01:09:38,183
(car door closes)

958
01:09:38,874 --> 01:09:40,581
(car engine starts)

959
01:09:45,948 --> 01:09:48,690
(cell phone chiming)

960
01:09:51,420 --> 01:09:52,899
Hi.

961
01:09:52,955 --> 01:09:54,798
(horn honking)

962
01:09:58,360 --> 01:09:59,634
(tires screech)

963
01:10:01,363 --> 01:10:03,775
- Sorry.
- That wasn't five minutes.

964
01:10:03,832 --> 01:10:05,209
No, I know, it's...

965
01:10:05,267 --> 01:10:06,712
Oh, quick. Right.

966
01:10:06,769 --> 01:10:09,750
Traffic was dreadful.
I'm really sorry.

967
01:10:10,372 --> 01:10:11,646
So this is it, is it?

968
01:10:11,707 --> 01:10:14,187
No, it's a spectacularly
elaborate wind-up, Dad.

969
01:10:14,243 --> 01:10:16,245
Yeah, sorry.
Sorry, point taken.

970
01:10:16,312 --> 01:10:17,655
Have you heard from Mum?

971
01:10:17,713 --> 01:10:19,317
Uh, no, no, but I phoned her

972
01:10:19,381 --> 01:10:21,141
and she's in a meeting,
but I left a message.

973
01:10:21,183 --> 01:10:22,685
- (grunts)
- Oh.

974
01:10:24,320 --> 01:10:25,560
Oh!

975
01:10:26,222 --> 01:10:27,792
Right. Okay.

976
01:10:27,856 --> 01:10:29,233
Off we go.

977
01:10:33,229 --> 01:10:34,230
(engine starts)

978
01:10:34,296 --> 01:10:37,300
- Dad, I think I'm gonna be sick.
- You're gonna be sick?

979
01:10:38,234 --> 01:10:39,269
(Susie groans)

980
01:10:39,335 --> 01:10:41,372
(crying)

981
01:10:41,437 --> 01:10:44,680
Oh, this whole thing's
such a load of shit.

982
01:10:44,740 --> 01:10:48,051
I mean, our gene pool alone
is bad enough.

983
01:10:48,110 --> 01:10:50,215
Workaholic meets curmudgeon

984
01:10:50,279 --> 01:10:52,023
- meets deranged 30-something.
- You're not a curmudgeon.

985
01:10:52,047 --> 01:10:54,584
- I was talking about you.
- I know, darling.

986
01:10:54,650 --> 01:10:56,493
The best thing you can do
is just relax,

987
01:10:56,552 --> 01:10:57,896
- calm down.
- Look, don't tell me to relax.

988
01:10:57,920 --> 01:11:00,799
Jesus. Just call Mum.

989
01:11:02,691 --> 01:11:03,965
Afternoon, I'm Emma.

990
01:11:04,026 --> 01:11:06,097
Hi, Emma. I'm Tony.
This is Susie.

991
01:11:06,161 --> 01:11:09,074
- How we doing?
- We're having a bit of a wobble.

992
01:11:09,131 --> 01:11:10,906
Oh, for Christ's sake, Dad.

993
01:11:10,966 --> 01:11:13,776
All right, I'll leave
you two to it, okay?

994
01:11:13,836 --> 01:11:16,612
- Where are you going?
- Isn't that what you want?

995
01:11:17,606 --> 01:11:20,052
Do you want me to stay?
Do you want me to go? Call Mum?

996
01:11:20,109 --> 01:11:21,281
Yes.

997
01:11:22,278 --> 01:11:24,258
Right, right.

998
01:11:25,481 --> 01:11:26,824
(door closes)

999
01:11:46,602 --> 01:11:48,377
(men laughing on TV)

1000
01:11:48,437 --> 01:11:50,212
Man on TV:
Good night, Harry.

1001
01:11:59,181 --> 01:12:01,593
(laughing on TV)

1002
01:12:01,650 --> 01:12:03,630
Man on TV: Flying Doctor
calling Wollumboola base.

1003
01:12:14,596 --> 01:12:16,439
Tony:
“Dear, Adrian and Veronica.

1004
01:12:18,901 --> 01:12:21,347
Hello, bitch,
and welcome to this letter.

1005
01:12:21,403 --> 01:12:22,711
(door opens)

1006
01:12:30,646 --> 01:12:33,058
A letter to you both
to wish you much joy.

1007
01:12:33,115 --> 01:12:35,435
- You certainly deserve one another.
- (typewriter dinging)

1008
01:12:37,886 --> 01:12:40,059
(sighs)

1009
01:12:42,124 --> 01:12:44,070
Indeed, I hope you get so involved

1010
01:12:44,126 --> 01:12:46,766
that the mutual damage
will be permanent.

1011
01:12:50,265 --> 01:12:52,245
Part of me hopes
you'll have a child

1012
01:12:52,301 --> 01:12:54,577
because I'm a great believer
in time's revenge.

1013
01:12:54,636 --> 01:12:57,276
Yay unto the next generation,
and all that.

1014
01:12:58,374 --> 01:12:59,614
But in fairness,

1015
01:12:59,675 --> 01:13:01,211
it would perhaps be
somewhat unjust

1016
01:13:01,276 --> 01:13:02,880
to inflict such ill will

1017
01:13:02,945 --> 01:13:05,118
on the fruit
of your poisonous Joins.

1018
01:13:11,820 --> 01:13:14,562
Adrian, if she hasn't
let you go all the way yet,

1019
