- Yes.

1263
01:31:03,357 --> 01:31:05,428
The one with the bad beard?

1264
01:31:07,762 --> 01:31:09,435
(whispering)

1265
01:31:14,769 --> 01:31:16,373
I'll be right back.

1266
01:31:27,415 --> 01:31:28,416
Hello.

1267
01:31:30,952 --> 01:31:32,932
Is there something
I can help you with?

1268
01:31:32,987 --> 01:31:36,127
- Do you want a chip?
- No, no, I'm fine.

1269
01:31:36,190 --> 01:31:38,932
On the menu it says
they're fat cut, hand cut.

1270
01:31:38,993 --> 01:31:40,637
But what it really means
is they're fat cut.

1271
01:31:40,661 --> 01:31:42,868
They've not actually
been cut by hand at all.

1272
01:31:44,465 --> 01:31:46,706
Uh, look, don't take this
the wrong way, but...

1273
01:31:46,767 --> 01:31:48,940
I'll do my best.
(chuckles)

1274
01:31:49,003 --> 01:31:50,880
I think, for whatever reason,

1275
01:31:50,938 --> 01:31:53,817
one of the people I look after
is a little uncomfortable

1276
01:31:53,875 --> 01:31:55,650
with you being here.

1277
01:31:55,710 --> 01:31:59,283
- Again.
- Oh, I'm sorry.

1278
01:31:59,347 --> 01:32:01,088
I didn't mean to upset anyone.
I'll leave.

1279
01:32:01,148 --> 01:32:03,719
If you don't mind,
can I ask who you are?

1280
01:32:03,784 --> 01:32:05,855
- Tony Webster.
- Uh, Ben.

1281
01:32:05,920 --> 01:32:07,464
- Do you mind if I sit down, Tony?
- Of course.

1282
01:32:07,488 --> 01:32:08,831
Cheers.

1283
01:32:10,625 --> 01:32:14,163
I was an old friend
of Adrian's father,

1284
01:32:14,228 --> 01:32:16,902
and I've recently become
reacquainted with his mother.

1285
01:32:16,964 --> 01:32:19,171
Oh, you'll understand, then.

1286
01:32:19,233 --> 01:32:21,509
She and I were
at university together.

1287
01:32:21,569 --> 01:32:24,106
Really? You don't look
old enough to have been at uni

1288
01:32:24,171 --> 01:32:27,175
- with Adrian's mum.
- You're too kind.

1289
01:32:27,241 --> 01:32:29,414
I was rather hoping to
bump into her here, but, uh...

1290
01:32:29,477 --> 01:32:31,889
Wait, wait, sorry.
Uh, bump into who?

1291
01:32:31,946 --> 01:32:34,153
Veronica.
Adrian's mother.

1292
01:32:35,816 --> 01:32:37,318
Um...

1293
01:32:37,385 --> 01:32:39,991
you understand I can't discuss
our clients' histories,

1294
01:32:40,054 --> 01:32:41,331
it's a matter of confidentiality.

1295
01:32:41,355 --> 01:32:43,164
- Yeah, of course.
- Um...

1296
01:32:43,224 --> 01:32:45,369
Now, if you are a friend of the family,
what you're saying, Tony,

1297
01:32:45,393 --> 01:32:47,339
doesn't make any sense.

1298
01:32:47,495 --> 01:32:49,372
Veronica is Adrian's sister.

1299
01:32:52,233 --> 01:32:55,544
Um, their mother, Sarah,
passed away six months ago.

1300
01:33:06,080 --> 01:33:08,390
- How did he seem?
- Cheerful.

1301
01:33:08,449 --> 01:33:10,986
Happy. Like himself.

1302
01:33:11,519 --> 01:33:13,055
Only more so.

1303
01:33:14,622 --> 01:33:17,330
As we said good-bye,
he told me he was in love.

1304
01:33:28,035 --> 01:33:31,346
You won't let Veronica get away
with too much, will you?

1305
01:33:32,306 --> 01:33:33,683
Sorry?

1306
01:33:35,042 --> 01:33:37,352
Don't let her get away
with too much.

1307
01:33:38,045 --> 01:33:39,353
Are we okay?

1308
01:33:41,449 --> 01:33:44,259
They seem very happy,
the five of them.

1309
01:33:45,453 --> 01:33:48,491
- You obviously do a good job.
- We try our best.

1310
01:33:50,157 --> 01:33:51,500
Good luck to you all.

1311
01:33:53,060 --> 01:33:54,368
I'm gonna head back
to the group.

1312
01:34:24,959 --> 01:34:27,030
(cell phone chiming)

1313
01:34:34,535 --> 01:34:36,113
Margaret: Please leave me
a message after the beep.

1314
01:34:36,137 --> 01:34:38,174
- (beeps)
- Margaret, it's me again.

1315
01:34:38,239 --> 01:34:39,445
Yeah, uh, this is it.

1316
01:34:39,507 --> 01:34:41,578
I think this is definitely it.
Where are you?

1317
01:34:42,710 --> 01:34:44,348
(cell phone beeps)

1318
01:35:04,699 --> 01:35:06,144
(sighs)

1319
01:35:07,368 --> 01:35:08,813
Tell me about your day.

1320
01:35:08,869 --> 01:35:10,314
My day?

1321
01:35:10,371 --> 01:35:12,749
Yeah. What you did.

1322
01:35:12,807 --> 01:35:15,617
Oh. Okay.
I went to High-gate.

1323
01:35:15,676 --> 01:35:17,952
To see a woman who I'd had
a relationship with

1324
01:35:18,012 --> 01:35:19,719
when I was an undergraduate.

1325
01:35:19,780 --> 01:35:21,953
We've recently become reacquainted,

1326
01:35:22,016 --> 01:35:23,859
but she wasn't there.

1327
01:35:24,919 --> 01:35:27,297
- Wasn't where?
- At home.

1328
01:35:27,354 --> 01:35:28,992
So what were you doing there?

1329
01:35:29,056 --> 01:35:31,161
I went to see her.

1330
01:35:31,225 --> 01:35:34,229
- But she wasn't there.
- No.

1331
01:35:34,295 --> 01:35:37,367
I waited around a bit, outside...

1332
01:35:37,431 --> 01:35:38,535
at the station.

1333
01:35:38,599 --> 01:35:41,273
So you're stalking her?
You're her stalker.

1334
01:35:41,335 --> 01:35:43,337
- No.
- Yes, you are.

1335
01:35:43,404 --> 01:35:44,747
No. Not at all, no.

1336
01:35:44,805 --> 01:35:46,580
No, moving on.

1337
01:35:46,640 --> 01:35:48,642
We broke up is the point.

1338
01:35:48,709 --> 01:35:51,383
While we were
still at university.

1339
01:35:51,445 --> 01:35:54,722
And not long after, she formed
a relationship with my best friend.

1340
01:35:56,550 --> 01:35:58,689
And I wrote them both

1341
01:35:58,753 --> 01:36:00,562
a very nasty letter.

1342
01:36:02,256 --> 01:36:04,702
And recently, I've been working
under the assumption

1343
01:36:04,759 --> 01:36:06,170
that they'd had a child together

1344
01:36:06,227 --> 01:36:09,401
shortly before my best friend
committed suicide.

1345
01:36:09,463 --> 01:36:11,534
But now it appears
that the mother of that child

1346
01:36:11,599 --> 01:36:14,637
wasn't my ex-girlfriend,
but it was her mother.

1347
01:36:14,702 --> 01:36:17,842
And I can only assume
that it was my...

1348
01:36:17,905 --> 01:36:20,351
horrible letter that
in some way pushed the...

1349
01:36:20,407 --> 01:36:22,387
- (knocks on door)
- friend...

1350
01:36:22,443 --> 01:36:24,548
(door opens)

1351
01:36:25,379 --> 01:36:26,380
(Susie clears throat)

1352
01:36:26,447 --> 01:36:28,051
Emma:
Hello again, Tony.

1353
01:36:28,115 --> 01:36:30,186
- Emma.
- Oh, hi, Emma.

1354
01:36:30,251 --> 01:36:31,821
- How we doing?
- (sighs)

1355
01:36:31,886 --> 01:36:34,730
I'd say holding up, just about.
(chuckles)

1356
01:36:34,789 --> 01:36:36,564
Emma: (softly)
I'll just check baby's head.

1357
01:36:38,025 --> 01:36:40,164
No, no, no.
Dad, stay.

1358
01:36:40,761 --> 01:36:42,138
Just for a bit.

1359
01:36:44,331 --> 01:36:45,833
You can hold my hand.

1360
01:36:49,637 --> 01:36:51,639
(heart monitor beeping)

1361
01:36:57,211 --> 01:36:59,350
What's going on?

1362
01:36:59,413 --> 01:37:02,326
- I don't know what's going on.
- Tony: Everything's fine.

1363
01:37:06,754 --> 01:37:08,927
Dad, why isn't anyone
saying anything?

1364
01:37:08,989 --> 01:37:10,730
Everything's absolutely fine.

1365
01:37:10,791 --> 01:37:12,828
We're nearly there,
I promise you.

1366
01:37:15,129 --> 01:37:16,574
(breathing heavily)

1367
01:37:19,066 --> 01:37:21,205
Emma:
Susie, you have a baby.

1368
01:37:21,268 --> 01:37:22,679
Congratulations.

1369
01:37:32,880 --> 01:37:34,723
Why isn't he crying?

1370
01:37:35,783 --> 01:37:37,285
He's not crying.

1371
01:37:38,953 --> 01:37:40,497
- Can you see anything?
- He's fine. He's fine.

1372
01:37:40,521 --> 01:37:41,625
Why isn't he crying?

1373
01:37:41,689 --> 01:37:43,100
Excuse me, my daughter's asking,

1374
01:37:43,157 --> 01:37:44,830
why isn't her son crying?

1375
01:37:49,430 --> 01:37:51,467
(baby crying)

1376
01:37:54,001 --> 01:37:55,480
(laughing)

1377
01:37:59,707 --> 01:38:01,744
- So proud of you.
- (Susie chuckles)

1378
01:38:08,349 --> 01:38:10,522
- I wanna see him.
- Tony: Yeah.

1379
01:38:14,555 --> 01:38:17,195
- Baby.
- Ah, look.

1380
01:38:17,258 --> 01:38:18,999
Say hello to your mummy.

1381
01:38:19,059 --> 01:38:21,198
- (Susie laughing)
- There he is.

1382
01:38:31,872 --> 01:38:33,909
- It's very hot.
- Margaret: Thank you.

1383
01:38:45,719 --> 01:38:48,393
You don't have to stay here,
you know.

1384
01:38:48,455 --> 01:38:49,798
I want to.

1385
01:38:55,729 --> 01:38:58,869
Susie said you dealt
with everything very impressively.

1386
01:38:59,800 --> 01:39:03,270
I'm not an entirely redundant
member of this family, yet.

1387
01:39:04,338 --> 01:39:07,376
- I've never said you were.
- Haven't you?

1388
01:39:12,880 --> 01:39:14,689
Where are you going?

1389
01:39:14,748 --> 01:39:16,489
I'm gonna give you some space.

1390
01:39:16,550 --> 01:39:18,359
Fine. But, uh...

1391
01:39:19,386 --> 01:39:21,764
you may be interested to know,
you probably won't,

1392
01:39:21,822 --> 01:39:24,894
but I was planning on
making an apology to you.

1393
01:39:26,393 --> 01:39:28,669
For being insensitive,
being a bore,

1394
01:39:28,729 --> 01:39:31,107
for being a monumental
pain in the arse.

1395
01:39:32,933 --> 01:39:35,709
Maybe it's too little too late,
but I hope not.

1396
01:39:37,037 --> 01:39:38,983
I know, technically,

1397
01:39:39,039 --> 01:39:40,848
we're not supposed
to make pronouncements

1398
01:39:40,908 --> 01:39:43,047
of this nature anymore, but...

1399
01:39:44,011 --> 01:39:47,788
you and Susie are the two
most important people in my life.

1400
01:39:50,250 --> 01:39:53,322
Divorced, married,
makes no difference.

1401
01:39:58,659 --> 01:40:00,605
Well, there you are.

1402
01:40:03,964 --> 01:40:05,875
Despite what you might think...

1403
01:40:07,835 --> 01:40:10,748
I assure you, I'm trying.

1404
01:40:11,638 --> 01:40:13,549
(sighs)
(tapping on watch)

1405
01:40:17,411 --> 01:40:19,448
What's wrong with your watch?

1406
01:40:20,948 --> 01:40:22,621
It's stopped.

1407
01:40:38,132 --> 01:40:39,475
(chuckling)

1408
01:40:53,747 --> 01:40:56,921
- Come on, baby.
- (both chuckling)

1409
01:40:59,486 --> 01:41:00,726
Get you home.

1410
01:41:00,788 --> 01:41:03,200
- Leaving.
- (baby crying)

1411
01:41:03,257 --> 01:41:05,294
Leaving hospital.

1412
01:41:09,563 --> 01:41:13,067
Tony: How often do we
tell our own life story?

1413
01:41:13,133 --> 01:41:17,878
How often do we adjust,
embellish, make sly cuts?

1414
01:41:17,938 --> 01:41:20,111
And the longer life goes on,

1415
01:41:20,174 --> 01:41:24,316
the fewer are those around
to tell us our life is not our life.

1416
01:41:24,378 --> 01:41:27,325
It is just a story
we've told about our lives.

1417
01:41:28,615 --> 01:41:31,221
A story about our lives
told to others,

1418
01:41:31,285 --> 01:41:33,959
but mainly to ourselves.

1419
01:41:35,823 --> 01:41:37,461
Oh, hello.
How are you?

1420
01:41:38,225 --> 01:41:40,034
- Uh, what?
- Are you well?

1421
01:41:40,094 --> 01:41:42,404
- I'm fine.
- Want a coffee?

1422
01:41:42,996 --> 01:41:43,997
Y-Yeah.

1423
01:41:49,703 --> 01:41:51,478
- (sighs)
- Mm.

1424
01:41:53,273 --> 01:41:54,650
Thank you.

1425
01:41:54,708 --> 01:41:55,709
Could you, um...

1426
01:41:55,776 --> 01:41:57,619
could you sign here, please?
I just got...

1427
01:41:57,678 --> 01:41:58,952
(device beeping)

1428
01:42:02,382 --> 01:42:03,952
Thank you.

1429
01:42:05,419 --> 01:42:07,524
Great, thank you.

1430
01:42:07,588 --> 01:42:09,124
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1431
01:42:18,899 --> 01:42:21,505
(laughing)

1432
01:42:21,568 --> 01:42:25,641
Tony: "I've been turning over
in my mind the question of nostalgia,

1433
01:42:25,706 --> 01:42:27,947
and whether! Suffer from it.

1434
01:42:29,576 --> 01:42:31,715
I suppose I am nostalgic.

1435
01:42:32,813 --> 01:42:34,918
I think of my time with Margaret

1436
01:42:34,982 --> 01:42:37,519
and Susie's birth and her first years.

1437
01:42:38,719 --> 01:42:40,426
A bunch of kids in school.

1438
01:42:40,487 --> 01:42:41,898
(all laughing)

1439
01:42:44,458 --> 01:42:46,870
A girl dancing
for once in her life.

1440
01:42:46,927 --> 01:42:48,065
(squeals)

1441
01:42:50,130 --> 01:42:54,510
A secret horizontal gesture
beneath a sunlit Wisteria.

1442
01:42:58,539 --> 01:43:01,543
I think of Adrian's
definition of history.

1443
01:43:08,182 --> 01:43:11,163
I think of everything
that has happened in my life...

1444
01:43:12,152 --> 01:43:14,723
and how little
I have allowed to happen.

1445
01:43:15,322 --> 01:43:18,030
I, who neither won nor lost.

1446
01:43:18,892 --> 01:43:21,065
Who avoided being hurt

1447
01:43:21,128 --> 01:43:23,938
and called it
a capacity for survival.

1448
01:43:29,736 --> 01:43:32,979
I think of how our lives
got entwined

1449
01:43:33,040 --> 01:43:35,850
and went along together
for a time.

1450
01:43:35,909 --> 01:43:38,253
And when I look back,

1451
01:43:38,312 --> 01:43:41,088
now, on that time,
however brief...

1452
01:43:42,783 --> 01:43:45,992
I am moved
more than I thought possible.

1453
01:43:47,754 --> 01:43:49,495
Indeed, I'm sorry
that I have known nothing

1454
01:43:49,556 --> 01:43:51,661
of your life in the years since.

1455
01:43:52,693 --> 01:43:55,970
No doubt you could have taught
this old fool a thing or two.

1456
01:44:01,568 --> 01:44:03,570
Perhaps, in a way, you have.“

1457
01:44:08,542 --> 01:44:09,885
(knocks on door)

1458
01:44:16,250 --> 01:44:18,093
- Hello.
- Surprise!

1459
01:44:18,151 --> 01:44:19,391
- Lovely surprise.
- (chuckles)

1460
01:44:20,721 --> 01:44:22,132
Hello, Joshua.

1461
01:44:22,189 --> 01:44:24,533
- Say hello to "The Mudge."
- Hello, Mudge.

1462
01:44:24,591 --> 01:44:27,162
No, you are The Mudge.
Mum and I decided.

1463
01:44:27,227 --> 01:44:28,763
On account of
your being a curmudgeon.

1464
01:44:28,829 --> 01:44:31,241
(laughs)
How are you?

1465
01:44:31,298 --> 01:44:32,299
Good.

1466
01:44:32,366 --> 01:44:34,744
The NCT group
send their love to you.

1467
01:44:34,801 --> 01:44:36,212
Oh, that's nice.

1468
01:44:36,270 --> 01:44:40,309
We had a lovely lunch comparing
the damage done to our bodies.

1469
01:44:40,374 --> 01:44:43,082
- Vaginas and all.
- Oh, Joshua, cover your ears.

1470
01:44:43,143 --> 01:44:44,663
- Cover your ears.
- (Joshua squealing)

1471
01:44:46,146 --> 01:44:47,648
(Tony chuckling)

1472
01:44:47,714 --> 01:44:49,318
Susie:
Very good.

1473
01:44:51,852 --> 01:44:53,661
Tony:
You're a special young man.

1474
01:45:00,761 --> 01:45:02,763
(music playing)

